10:44:39 AM [express] GET /api/tasks 200 in 5ms :: [{"id":10,"companyId":1,"title":"Build Incremental Transaction & Chargeback Pipeline for Real-Time Risk Dashboards","description":"We need a reliable, incremental data pipeline that ingests card transactions and chargeback/dispute events from our core payments system and third-party processor feeds into the analytics warehouse. The goal is to enable near-real-time monitoring of fraud/chargeback rates by merchant, BIN, country, and channel (card present vs. card not present) while ensuring data quality, deduplication, and consistent business definitions. The pipeline should support late-arriving events (e.g., chargebacks created days after the original transaction) and allow analysts to slice metrics with consistent dimensions and timestamps. Please design the data model (fact/dimension or wide table approach), implement the pipeline, and add data quality checks and observability. We also need documentation and a handoff so analysts can build dashboards without reverse-engineering joins.","requestedBy":"Data Engineer","priority":"high","projectArea":"Data Engineering","recommendedRole":"Data Engineer","assignedRole":null,"difficulty":null,"status":"backlog","businessContext":null,"subtasks":null,"deliverables":null,"solutionNotes":null,"architectureNotes":null,"progressNotes":null,"githubLink":null,"documentationLink":null,"milestoneId":null,"createdAt":"2026-03-08T11:49:46.730Z"},{"id":9,"companyId":3,"title":"Build Daily Customer Cohort Retention & LTV Dataset for Subscription + One-Time Purchases","description":"We need a reliable, refreshable dataset to power retention and LTV reporting across both subscription orders and one-time purchases. Today, metrics are calculated ad hoc in Looker and spreadsheets, and different teams disagree on definitions (cohort start, refunds, churn, etc.).\n\nPlease design and implement a set of modeled tables (in our warehouse) that produce daily customer cohorts, retention curves, 